std::vector<std::string> plants(const std::string& diagram, const std::string& student) {
    // List of children in order
    const std::vector<std::string> children = {
        "Alice", "Bob", "Charlie", "David",
        "Eve", "Fred", "Ginny", "Harriet",
        "Ileana", "Joseph", "Kincaid", "Larry"
    };
    
    // Find the index of the student
    auto it = std::find(children.begin(), children.end(), student);
    int index = std::distance(children.begin(), it);
    
    // Split the diagram into rows
    std::istringstream iss(diagram);
    std::string row1, row2;
    std::getline(iss, row1);
    std::getline(iss, row2);
    
    // Each child has 2 plants per row, so calculate the start and end indices
    int start = 2 * index;
    
    // Get the plants from both rows
    std::vector<std::string> result;
    
    // Process first row
    for (int i = start; i < start + 2; i++) {
        switch (row1[i]) {
            case 'G': result.push_back("grass"); break;
            case 'C': result.push_back("clover"); break;
            case 'R': result.push_back("radishes"); break;
            case 'V': result.push_back("violets"); break;
        }
    }
    
    // Process second row
    for (int i = start; i < start + 2; i++) {
        switch (row2[i]) {
            case 'G': result.push_back("grass"); break;
            case 'C': result.push_back("clover"); break;
            case 'R': result.push_back("radishes"); break;
            case 'V': result.push_back("violets"); break;
        }
    }
    
    return result;
}

}  // namespace kindergarten_garden
